nomic%20Affairs%20adviser%2C%20Raina%2C%20while%20addressing%20the%20closing%20plenary%20session%20of%20the%20summit%2C%20said%20that%20the%20delegation%20was%20not%20allowed%20to%20speak%20before%20the%20adoption%20of%20the%20deal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20regret%20to%20say%20that%20this%20document%20is%20nothing%20more%20than%20an%20optical%20illusion.%20This%2C%20in%20our%20opinion%2C%20will%20not%20address%20the%20enormity%20of%20the%20challenge%20we%20all%20face.%20Therefore%2C%20we%20oppose%20the%20adoption%20of%20this%20document%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%24300%20billion%20does%20not%20address%20the%20needs%20and%20priorities%20of%20developing%20countries.%20It%20is%20incompatible%20with%20the%20principle%20of%20CBDR%20(Common%20but%20Differentiated%20Responsibilities)%20and%20equity%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20battle%20with%20the%20impact%20of%20climate%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20Raina%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20negotiator%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20very%20unhappy%2C%20disappointed%20with%20the%20process%2C%20and%20object%20to%20the%20adoption%20of%20this%20agenda.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESupporting%20India%2C%20Nigeria%20said%20the%20%24300%20billion%20climate%20finance%20package%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bjoke%26quot%3B.%20Malawi%20and%20Bolivia%20also%20lent%20support%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbout%20The%20Deal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agreement%20would%20provide%20%24300%20billion%20annually%20by%202035%2C%20boosting%20rich%20countries'%20previous%20commitment%20to%20provide%20%24100%20billion%20per%20year%20in%20climate%20finance%20by%202020.%20That%20earlier%20goal%20was%20met%20two%20years%20late%2C%20in%202022%2C%20and%20expires%20in%202025.%20The%20deal%20also%20lays%20the%20groundwork%20for%20next%20year's%20climate%20summit%2C%20to%20be%20held%20in%20the%20Amazon%20rainforest%20of%20Brazil%2C%20where%20countries%20are%20meant%20to%20map%20out%20the%20next%20decade%20of%20climate%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20summit%20cut%20to%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20debate%20over%20the%20financial%20responsibility%20of%20industrialized%20countries%20-%20whose%20historic%20use%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20has%20caused%20the%20bulk%20of%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20-%20to%20compensate%20others%20for%20worsening%20damage%20from%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20laid%20bare%20divisions%20between%20wealthy%20governments%20constrained%20by%20tight%20domestic%20budgets%20and%20developing%20nations%20reeling%20from%20the%20costs%20of%20storms%2C%20floods%20and%20droughts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENegotiations%20had%20been%20due%20to%20finish%20on%20Friday%20but%20ran%20into%20overtime%20as%20representatives%20from%20nearly%20200%20countries%20struggled%20to%20reach%20consensus.%20Talks%20were%20interrupted%20on%20Saturday%20as%20some%20developing%20countries%20and%20island%20nations%20walked%20away%20in%20frustration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnited%20Nations%20climate%20chief%20Simon%20Stiell%20acknowledged%20the%20difficult%20negotiations%20that%20led%20to%20the%20agreement%20but%20hailed%20the%20outcome%20as%20an%20insurance%20policy%20for%20humanity%20against%20global%20warming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20has%20been%20a%20difficult%20journey%2C%20but%20we've%20delivered%20a%20deal...This%20deal%20will%20keep%20the%20clean%20energy%20boom%20growing%20and%20protect%20billions%20of%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20Stiell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20like%20any%20insurance%20policy%20-%20it%20only%20works%20-%20if%20the%20premiums%20are%20paid%20in%20full%2C%20and%20on%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732439520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fr8blid5o_cop20-reuters_625x300_24_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ftoo-little-too-late-india-rejects-300-billion-cop29-climate-deal-7093183%22%2C%2