pute%20over%20a%20dog%20named%20Tank%2C%20whose%20story%20continues%20to%20draw%20attention.%20The%20saga%20began%20in%202005%20when%20Tank%2C%20a%20St.%20Bernard%2C%20was%20separated%20from%20his%20Louisiana%20owners%2C%20Steve%20and%20Dorreen%20Couture%2C%20during%20Hurricane%20Katrina.%20Tank%20was%20later%20taken%20to%20the%20Pinellas%20Humane%20Society%20in%20Florida%2C%20where%20Ms%20Bondi%2C%20a%20prominent%20animal%20rights%20advocate%2C%20adopted%20him%20and%20renamed%20him%20Noah.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Bondi%2C%20who%20served%20as%20Florida's%20attorney%20general%2C%20was%20known%20for%20her%20active%20support%20of%20animal%20rights%2C%20even%20promoting%20causes%20like%20the%202018%20Florida%20ballot%20measure%20to%20ban%20dog%20racing.%20But%20her%20involvement%20with%20Tank%20stirred%20controversy%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20dog's%20original%20owners%20tracked%20him%20down%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Bondi%20argued%20that%20Tank%20had%20been%20seriously%20neglected%20by%20the%20Coutures%2C%20citing%20medical%20issues%20like%20heartworms%20that%20had%20severely%20affected%20the%20dog's%20health.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20was%20dying%20from%20heartworms.%20They%20had%20filled%20his%20heart%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ocala.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2F2006%2F05%2F22%2Ffamily-fights-to-get-back-dogs-katrina-forced-them-to-give-up%2F31159332007%2F%C2%A0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20St.%20Petersburg%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CI%20took%20a%20dog%20who%20was%20a%20walking%20skeleton.%20That's%20what%20was%20wrong%20with%20him%20before%20the%20hurricane.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Coutures%20denied%20these%20allegations%2C%20claiming%20that%20the%20heartworm%20condition%20was%20long-standing%2C%20and%20sought%20to%20reclaim%20their%20pet.%20In%20response%2C%20Ms%20Bondi%20insisted%20that%20she%20was%20providing%20a%20better%20environment%20for%20Tank.%20%E2%80%9C